			<td valign="top">
				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I think what you're asking is how you update &quot;portions&quot; of the pattern table data in PPU RAM, without starting from the beginning ($0000).  Your use of the term &quot;&quot;rows&quot;&quot; makes this a little confusing, but I think I know what you mean.  The answer should be somewhat obvious:<br /><br />In your setupChr routine, you explicitly set the PPU address to $0000 (<tt style="margin-left: 2px; margin-right: 2px; padding:3px; background-color: #3355aa; color: white;">LDA #$00 / ... / STA $2006 / STA $2006</tt>).  Writes to $2007 will begin there.  So if you wanted to start updating pattern table data at some other location, you'd need to keep track of that yourself within your program (or hard-code addresses) and set $2006 to wherever you want (in $0000-1FFF).<br /><br />For learning, start with hard-coded addresses.  It would be worthwhile for you to use an emulator that lets you view (and/or edit) PPU RAM (ex. FCEUX's &quot;Hex Editor&quot; debug menu option).<br /><br />Also recommend you review the <a href="http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/PPU_memory_map" class="postlink">PPU RAM memory map layout</a> and the <a href="http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/PPU_pattern_tables" class="postlink">pattern table data layout</a>.<br /><br />Tile #0 = $0000-000F<br />Tile #1 = $0010-001F<br />Tile #2 = $0020-002F<br />...<br /><br />And so on.  So depending on how long a &quot;&quot;row&quot;&quot; is to you (probably 16 tiles), you can easily determine what the starting address should be to update &quot;the 3rd or 4th row&quot; of pattern table data.<br /><br />All this stuff is documented: <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/PPU">http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/PPU</a><!-- m --><br /><br />Also, this looks syntactically wrong (how/why the assembler you're using allowed it is beyond me): <tt style="margin-left: 2px; margin-right: 2px; padding:3px; background-color: #3355aa; color: white;">LDA &#40;#$00&#41;,y</tt> should be <tt style="margin-left: 2px; margin-right: 2px; padding:3px; background-color: #3355aa; color: white;">LDA &#40;$00&#41;,y</tt><br /><br />Edit: removed some stuff about $2005/$2000.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

