			<td valign="top">
				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">There are 2 LDX, the second one should probably be LDA. It would also be a good idea to include a $2000 to select PPU address increments of 1 byte, rather than 32.<br /><br />As for your loop, there are several things wrong with it:<br /><br />1- You didn't reset Y to 0 before entering the loop. That will result in tiles being read from the wrong address.<br /><br />2- The first BNE LoopStart is completely wrong. When Y doesn't overflow, you're only supposed to skip the INC $01, no the entire rest of the loop. This will result in the wrong number of tiles being updated, because you're completely skipping the counting of tiles.<br /><br />3- TileCounter is supposed to count tiles, not bytes. You should use X to count 16 bytes (the amount of bytes in a tile), and have an outer loop count tiles.<br /><br />4- You are never storing the decremented TileCounter back, so it will never change and the loop will never end. In fact, you can use DEC TileCount instead of the much slower LDA, SEC, SBC, STA sequence.<br /><br />That's about all I can see wrong with the code. see if you can fix it based on these notes. It would be much better you you understood why it isn't working then if I gave you the whole fixed code.</div>

